FORMER SABC
boss and ABSA deputy CEO Peter Matlare (61) has died due to Covid-19
complications. Matlare has
held the position of CEO and Executive Director at Tiger Brands Ltd, was an
Executive Director-Commercial at Vodacom SA, Chief Strategy and Chairman at
National Association of Broadcasters. Saddened
Professor Thuli Madonsela expressed shock at the news of Matlare’s death. “Covid-19
has robbed us of another professional in his prime. Heartfelt condolences to
the family, friends and colleagues,” said Madonsela.